<p>At 20:52, The COEWS detected that SCP-5092-1 had dematerialized. At 20:53, the O5 council voted 13-0 to end the code black emergency and Protocol 34.</p>
<p>Following Incident 5092-1-A, SCP-5092 was reclassified and new containment procedures were written, including the creation of Site-143 and MTF Theta-20, tasked with containing SCP-5092.</p>
</div>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><strong>Incident 5092-1-B, 2012/6/22</strong></p>
</div>
<div class="blockquote">
<p>At 19:55, The COEWS detected that SCP-5092-1 had manifested 81&#160;000km away from Earth and would collide in 1hr and 15m at 21:10.</p>
<p>At 19:57, Overseer Command declared a code black emergency and enacted Protocol 34. (Protocol 27 could not be enacted due to the lack of notice to the object's arrival). At 19:58, Theta-20 Agents attempted and failed to contact the President.</p>
<p>At 20:15, MTF Theta-20 successfully neutralized the threat.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">⮝&nbsp;Show&nbsp;Containment&nbsp;Log</a></div>
