<h1 id="toc0"><span>Department of Spectral Phenomena</span></h1>
<p><span style="font-size:200%;">Spectral Entity No. 556</span></p>
</div>
<br />
<strong>Status:</strong> Active, SCP Classification Pending
<p><strong>Location:</strong> USA, District of Columbia, particularly the area surrounding Capitol Hill</p>
<p><strong>Description:</strong> SE-556 is a man who appears to be in his late 70's (although ectoplasm dating shows they are actually about 600 years old). They wear black boots, dark pants, a long brown trenchcoat, a pair of round glasses, and a dark trilby hat with a removable feather attached to its side in an almost magnetic fashion.</p>
<p>According to the <a target="_blank" href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-4973">Hollow-Kessler</a> Spectral Classification System, SE-556 is a Class II Spectral Entity (It lacks malevolence and expresses a very limited ability to interact with the physical world).</p>
<p><strong>Behaviour:</strong> For most of the day, SE-556 is fairly dormant. They will wander from street to street occasionally but spend most of their day sitting on benches in either parks or the wharf (next to Potomac River). While sitting, they may watch pedestrians or animals, read outdated newspapers (Newspapers are also spectral), stare up at the sky, or sleep. Notably, every day at around 7:52 PM, SE-556 seems to produce a 'portal' of some kind, and step through it, only to return ten minutes later. Occasionally, SE-556 can be seen toying with its hat feather prior to this event.</p>
<p><strong>Addendum:</strong> Analysis of SE-556's behavior by the psychological division has concluded that SE-556 is experiencing the early stages of spectro-cognitive degradation disorder.</p>
